The body of a Nyandarua county employee has been found dumped along Ol Kalou - Nyahururu road near the Nyandarua Institute of Science Technology. Mary Mundothi who was a Community Development Assistant officer in Ndaragwa subcounty was discovered dead on Saturday by a resident. Nyandarua county police commander Gideon Ngumi said they suspected that the woman was raped before being murdered. "Police rushed to the scene and found the body which had severe head injuries and a deep cut in the left cheek,” Ngumi said. The police boss said they had information that the woman was travelling back home from Nairobi when she was attacked. Police are probing the incident to ensure the offenders are brought to book. Nyandarua Governor Francis Kimemia condemned the incident and called for a speedy investigation and the arrest of the culprits. "I am pleased to note that security agencies have since taken up the matter into which we now expect speedy and conclusive investigations,” the county boss said. The body was moved to the Nyahururu County Referral Hospital mortuary awaiting postmortem examination.